  "question": "Carlos is planting a lemon tree. The tree will cost $90 to plant. Each year it will grow 7 lemons, which he can sell for $1.5 each. It costs $3 a year to water and feed the tree. How many years will it take before he starts earning money on the lemon tree?",
  "prompt": "Carlos is planting a lemon tree. The tree will cost $90 to plant. Each year it will grow 7 lemons, which he can sell for $1.5 each. It costs $3 a year to water and feed the tree. How many years will it take before he starts earning money on the lemon tree?\n\nShow your work briefly and put the final answer in \\boxed{}.",
  "gold_answer": "13",
  "generated_text": "To determine how many years it takes for Carlos to start earning money, we need to calculate the profit for each year.\n\n1.  **Analyze the costs and revenues:**\n    *   **Planting Cost:** $\\$90$ (This happens once at the beginning).\n    *   **Annual Water/Feed Cost:** $\\$3$ per year.\n    *   **Lemon Production:** The tree produces 7 lemons per year.\n    *   **Lemon Sales Price:** $\\$1.50$ per lemon.\n    *   **Earnings per Year:** $7 \\text{ lemons} \\times \\$1.50/\\text{lemon} = \\$10.50$.\n\n2.  **Calculate the annual profit:**\n    *   $\\text{Profit} = \\text{Revenue} - \\text{Costs}$\n    *   $\\text{Profit} = \\$10.50 - \\$3 = \\$7.50$ per year.\n\n3.  **Determine when profit becomes positive (first year of earning):**\n    *   Carlos spends $\\$90$ to start the tree.\n    *   He earns money in the year the tree produces lemons.\n    *   Let $n$ be the number of years the tree has been growing.\n    *   At the end of year 1, the tree has produced lemons. The cost of planting is already paid. The water/feeding costs for year 1 have been incurred.\n    *   The profit calculation for the first year is: $\\$10.50 - \\$3 = \\$7.50$.\n    *   Since the profit ($\\$7.50$) is greater than zero, he makes a profit in the first year.\n\nTherefore, he starts earning money in Year 1.\n\n\\boxed{1}\n",
